column1: Marks: N/A means this feature is prohibited to set when this IO type is selected

column2: INTERNAL means use internal VREF voltage for INR mode
column3: VREF1_LOAD means use external input VREF voltage for INR mode
column5: 1 pad on this bank should be set to VREF1_LOAD input mode .

column2: This IO Type is used only when at least one IO is set to SSTL/HSTL and VREF feature is set to VREF1_LOAD.
MIPI Input is only support on Top side.VCCX=2.5V/3.3V
Internal VREF Mode: use internal VREF
column3: Bank VCCIO must equal the voltage of input IO_TYPE at this mode
column4: External VREF Mode: use External input REF voltage
column5: Bank VCCIO should ≥ the voltage of input IO_TPYE at this mode.
